            <div class="slides_container"><div id="21343-slide1"><img src="http://homepost.kpbs.org/files/2012/03/425616_10150704308647628_93535462627_9350899_114405775_n-620x412.jpg" width="620" height="412" /><h6>U.S. Navy / Mass Communication Specialist Seaman George M. Bell <a href="#" class="slide-permalink">permalink</a></h6><p>Dan Rather arrives on Vinson's flight deck, greeted by Executive Officer Cmdr. Paul Spedero</p></div><div id="21343-slide2"><img src="http://homepost.kpbs.org/files/2012/03/419706_10150704309892628_93535462627_9350911_2066688270_n-620x412.jpg" width="620" height="412" /><h6>Mass Communication Specialist Seaman George M. Bell / U.S. Navy <a href="#" class="slide-permalink">permalink</a></h6><p>Dan Rather prepares to have dinner</p></div><div id="21343-slide3" data-src="http://homepost.kpbs.org/files/2012/03/425831_10150704307632628_93535462627_9350892_1972276425_n-620x412.jpg*620*412" /><h6>U.S. Navy <a href="#" class="slide-permalink">permalink</a></h6><p>Dan Rather dines with Vinson crew</p></div><div id="21343-slide4" data-src="http://homepost.kpbs.org/files/2012/03/427008_10150704309627628_93535462627_9350908_1194349056_n-620x412.jpg*620*412" /><h6>Mass Communication Specialist Seaman George M. Bell / U.S. Navy <a href="#" class="slide-permalink">permalink</a></h6><p>Dan Rather talks with Commanding Officer Capt. Kent D. Whalen</p></div><div id="21343-slide5"><img src="http://homepost.kpbs.org/files/2012/03/422826_10150704315177628_93535462627_9350962_876526893_n-620x412.jpg" width="620" height="412" /><h6>Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class James R. Evans / U.S. Navy <a href="#" class="slide-permalink">permalink</a></h6><p>Dan Rather interviews pilot Lt. Mike Shaughnessy in the cockpit of an F/A-18E Super Hornet</p></div></div></div><script>jQuery( document ).ready( function() { loadSlideshow( 21343, 'http://homepost.kpbs.org/2012/03/dan-rather-visits-uss-carl-vinson-slideshow/', 5 ) } );</script>
<p>Veteran war journalist and longtime CBS anchor <a href="http://www.biography.com/people/dan-rather-9452277">Dan Rather</a> visited the USS Carl Vinson this past weekend. Rather was interviewing Sailors and shooting footage for his HDNet program &#8220;<a href="http://www.facebook.com/USSVINSON#!/DanRatherReports">Dan Rather Reports</a>.&#8221; The <a href="http://www.facebook.com/USSVINSON#!/USSVINSON">USS Vinson Facebook page</a> says the program featuring footage from Rather&#8217;s Vinson visit will air March 27th.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s a slideshow of Rather&#8217;s visits. (Can you believe he&#8217;s 80?) Based on the numerous comments on the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/USSVINSON#!/USSVINSON">Vinson&#8217;s Facebook page</a>, the crew was thrilled to have him aboard.</p>
        </div> <!-- #post-## --> 
    
